 release that's not the most recent, for whatever legacy reasons, it is helpful to have documentation.\r\n\r\nAlso, I assume Cassandra will eventually get proper packaging for different environments, and users may install it without discovery from the wiki.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=euphoria","name":"euphoria","emailAddress":"michael dot greene at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Michael Greene","active":true},"created":"2009-04-29T16:13:43.773+0000","updated":"2009-04-29T16:13:43.773+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12424164/comment/12704182","id":"12704182","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=johanoskarsson","name":"johanoskarsson","emailAddress":"johan dot oskarsson at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Johan Oskarsson","active":true},"body":"This is pretty much all I'm going to push for adding to the release readme file, I don't think it's too much to maintain.\r\n\r\nPersonally when I download some new tool I want to have a clear and concise, step by step guide on how to get it to do something. Even though Cassandra is in quite a niche market I think there's a high risk of losing potential users simply because they get stuck on the installation procedure. There's plenty of other problems out there for them, we should make this part the easy bit :)","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=johanoskarsson","name":"johanoskarsson","emailAddress":"johan dot oskarsson at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Johan Oskarsson","active":true},"created":"2009-04-29T16:18:05.212+0000","updated":"2009-04-29T16:18:05.212+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12424164/comment/12704202","id":"12704202","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sandeep_tata","name":"sandeep_tata","emailAddress":"sandeep dot tata at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Sandeep Tata","active":true},"body":"+1 to the quickstart info in the README. \r\n\r\nI agree with Michael that the wiki will probably point only to the latest version (although we could archive installation instructions for older releases).\r\nI'd be wary of adding any other info that might be duplicated on the wiki, but installation + sample insert/read are good things to make easy.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sandeep_tata","name":"sandeep_tata","emailAddress":"sandeep dot tata at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","2